        "text": "Extract data from this Access Point dashboard screenshot. \nIdentify all rows containing: AP Name, RSSI (dBm), CU (%), and Active User.\n\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR VALUES:\n1. For 'rssi_dbm', you MUST append the 'dbm' unit text at the end of the value (e.g., \"-70,54dbm\" or \"-10dbm\").\n2. For 'cu_percent', you MUST append the '%' unit text at the end of the value (e.g., \"56,4%\" or \"75,8%\").\n3. Make sure to preserve the comma format for decimals if present in the image.\n\nReturn the result as a strict raw JSON array, without any markdown formatting, backticks, or 'json' text wrapper. \n\nExpected format:\n[\n  {\n    \"ap_name\": \"AP_Name_Example\",\n    \"rssi_dbm\": \"-70,54dbm\",\n    \"cu_percent\": \"56,4%\",\n    \"access_user\": 1,\n    \"ap_status\": \"online\"\n  }\n]\n",
        "inputType": "binary",
        "options": {}
      },
